Whait it means?
-This involves clearly explaining how tasks are done, including the steps, procedures, rules, and standards that guide work in an organization.
-This ensures that everyone understands what to do, how to do it, and when to do it.

Why it is important?
-Ensures consistency in performing tasks
-Prevents mistakes and accidents
-Helps new employees learn quickly
-Improves efficiency and quality of work


How it is communicated
-Verbal Instructions (meetings, briefings)
-Written Documents (manuals, SOPs, memos)
-Demonstrations or training
-Digital tools (emails, chat, videos)
Examples
-Caregiving setting
  >A senior caregiver explains the proper steps in feeding a patient (ex. handwashing, correct positioning, checking food temperature)
-Office Setting
  >A supervisor sends an email outlining the process for submitting reports (deadline, format, approval steps.)
-Hotel/Housekeeping
  >A manager demonstrates the standard process of cleaning rooms (ex... shit!!!0
-Construction Site
  >A team leader explains the safety procedures before starting work (wear PPE, inspect tools)

This means guiding conversations among trainees or workers to share ideas, solve problems, and improve understanding of tasks.
The trainer acts as a facilitator, not just a speaker - encouraging participation, asking questions, and keeping the discussion focused on.... (p0ta!!!)

Key roles of the Trainer:
-Set a clear topic or objective
-Encourage active participation from all learners
-Ask open-ended questions
-Manage time and keep the discussion on track
-Summarize key points and give feedback
Examples:
-Caregiving training
  >The trainer leads a discussion on proper patient handling
  >Asks: What  risks can gappen if we lift a patient incorrectly?
-Workplace Communication Lesson
  >The trainer facilitates a discussion about common communication problems at work.
  >Learners share real-life situations (misunderstood instructors, conflicts)
-Assessment Prepration
  >Before a competency assessment, the trainer leads a discussion on assessment procedures and expectations
-Problem-Solving activity
  >The trainer presents a workplace scenario (ex. conflict between co-workers)
  >Learners discuss possible solutions



IDENTIFY AND COMMUNICATE ISSUES ARISING IN THE WORKPLACE
This competency means that the trainer is able to recognize problems or issues that occur during training or in a simulated/workplace
environment and communicate them clearly and professionally to the appropriate people (learners, supervisors, or management)

Key responsibilities of the Trainer
-Identify issues early (observe behavior, performance, end environment)
-Analyze the cause of the problem
-Communicate clearly and calmly
-Use appropriate channels (discussio , report, feedback, session)
-Suggest solutions or corrective actions


